From 8c98528d1902ad2f5b06e0b1113427afa2e2e6f7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 15:51:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] duct-tape: cancel wait_timer in thread_unblock

XNU's thread_unblock() cancels a thread's armed wait_timer when the thread is
woken; duct-tape only did so in dtape_thread_destroy(). A timed wait
(pthread_cond_timedwait etc.) arms thread->wait_timer via
waitq_assert_wait64_locked(); if that wait is woken EARLY -- by a signal or a
normal condvar/mutex wakeup before its deadline -- the timer stayed armed and
later fired thread_timer_expire() -> clear_wait_internal(THREAD_TIMED_OUT),
delivering a SPURIOUS timeout to whatever the thread was doing at that point
(typically an unrelated deadline-less psynch wait). The bogus ETIMEDOUT
zeroed the condvar (ECVCLEARED) and stranded a waiter, producing the
intermittent 'brew fetch' hang.

Cancel the timer in thread_unblock(), matching XNU sched_prim.c. The
timer-expiry path is safe: thread_timer_expire() clears wait_timer_is_set
before clear_wait_internal()->thread_go()->thread_unblock(), so the cancel is
skipped on that path.

Refs dar-gwn.2.
---
 duct-tape/src/thread.c | 17 +++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+)

diff --git a/duct-tape/src/thread.c b/duct-tape/src/thread.c
index f4ce909677bfe659e948a04d477b1ce9003b2bc6..6a28d328a37195a7d6383a4224334a3c4ca902c0 100644
--- a/duct-tape/src/thread.c
+++ b/duct-tape/src/thread.c
@@ -549,6 +549,23 @@ wait_result_t thread_block(thread_continue_t continuation) {
 boolean_t thread_unblock(thread_t xthread, wait_result_t wresult) {
 	dtape_thread_t* thread = dtape_thread_for_xnu_thread(xthread);
 	thread->xnu_thread.wait_result = wresult;
+
+	// Cancel the wait timer if one was armed for a timed wait. XNU's
+	// thread_unblock() does this; duct-tape previously only cancelled it in
+	// dtape_thread_destroy(). Without it, a timed wait that is woken early
+	// (e.g. by a signal or a normal condvar/mutex wakeup before its deadline)
+	// leaves its wait_timer armed. The stale timer later fires
+	// thread_timer_expire() -> clear_wait_internal(THREAD_TIMED_OUT), which
+	// delivers a SPURIOUS timeout to whatever the thread is doing then --
+	// typically a subsequent deadline-less psynch wait -- aborting it with
+	// ETIMEDOUT and stranding a condvar/mutex handoff (intermittent hang).
+	if (thread->xnu_thread.wait_timer_is_set) {
+		if (timer_call_cancel(&thread->xnu_thread.wait_timer)) {
+			thread->xnu_thread.wait_timer_active--;
+		}
+		thread->xnu_thread.wait_timer_is_set = FALSE;
+	}
+
 	dtape_hooks->thread_resume(thread->context);
 	return TRUE;
 };
